**Cooldown Timer**
================

A simple cooldown timer that prevents repeated actions within a specified time frame.

### Code

```javascript
class CooldownTimer {
  constructor(duration) {
    this.duration = duration; // time in milliseconds
    this.lastActivated = 0; // timestamp of last activation
  }

  isReady() {
    return Date.now() - this.lastActivated >= this.duration;
  }

  activate() {
    if (this.isReady()) {
      this.lastActivated = Date.now();
      return true;
    } else {
      return false;
    }
  }
}

// Example usage:
const cooldown = new CooldownTimer(3000); // 3-second cooldown
console.log(cooldown.activate()); // returns: false (cooldown not ready)
setTimeout(() => {
  console.log(cooldown.activate()); // returns: true (cooldown ready)
}, 3000);
```

### Explanation

*   The `CooldownTimer` class takes a `duration` parameter, which specifies the time in milliseconds between activations.
*   The `isReady()` method checks whether the cooldown has expired by comparing the current timestamp with the last activation time.

